headline: Prologis (PLD) Valuation Check After 27% Share Price Gain Over the Past Year
summary: Prologis (PLD) has quietly outperformed the wider real estate sector this year, and with the stock up about 27% over the past year, investors are asking whether the current price still makes sense. See our latest analysis for Prologis. That move has been powered less by short term excitement and more by steady confidence, with the 90 day share price return of 11.49 percent feeding into a 12 month total shareholder return of 26.88 percent. headline: What Prologis (PLD)'s Q4 Earnings Reveal About Sustaining Its Logistics Leasing Momentum
summary: In recent days, investors have been watching Prologis closely ahead of its now-completed Q4 2025 earnings release, following previously reported strong Q3 results that highlighted solid operational execution and high portfolio occupancy. This renewed attention, reinforced by continued positive analyst sentiment, underscores how closely the market is tracking Prologis’ ability to sustain leasing strength and operational momentum in logistics real estate.
